nother attempt. Adding a source jar to the JVM might help ensure JaCoCo captures source lines.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating Java compilation issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m compiling all library sources into the test output. I wonder if there are duplicate classes in Java. While the original jar remains as testImplementation, having duplicates is okay, but I can't compile the same source more than once. I need to check for potential compile errors, especially with Java 25 and the old code that uses `yield`. Also, I should verify if Jsch 0.1.27 sources will compile and whether the essential jzlib is included. Let's list the source files for clarity.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_3uOqXKwuoR4aG83X39x9A14x|fc_04b7218707e23e620169f563582ed4819387f5762f9817a524\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted -type f | sed 's|.*/extracted/||' | sort | head -120 && rg -n \\\"com\\\\.jcraft\\\\.jzlib|jzlib\\\" /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted\", \"timeout\": 10}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"find /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted -type f | sed 's|.*/extracted/||' | sort | head -120 && rg -n \\\\\\\"com\\\\\\\\.jcraft\\\\\\\\.jzlib|jzlib\\\\\\\" /home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/main/extracted\\\",\\\"timeout\\\":10}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 438, \"output\": 1361, \"cacheRead\": 97280, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 99079, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cac